Quote: Two years after the second Company settlement, Nelson, was established in 1841, there was a serious incident (termed by the settlers the `Wairau massacre') when Captain Arthur Wakefield and several other Europeans were killed while attempting to arrest two turbulent chiefs, Te Rauparaha and Te Rangihaeata, ostensibly for burning surveyors, huts, but in reality for resisting the survey of land which the Maoris denied having sold.
